## Mapping designer — excluded items still shown after reset

### Context
`resetAllMappings()` cleared `MappingState.config.entities/relationships` but
did not call `_stampExcludedFlags()`. The `excluded` boolean lives on the
ontology objects inside `MappingState.loadedOntology`; it is only written by
`_stampExcludedFlags()`. Without the call, every class/property that was
previously excluded kept `excluded: true` even after the reset, so navigating
back to the designer showed them as excluded.

### Changes
1. `src/front/static/global/js/mapping-information.js` — call
   `_stampExcludedFlags()` immediately after wiping `MappingState.config` in
   `resetAllMappings()`, before the API calls, so the ontology objects are
   clean before any downstream render.

### Modified files
- `src/front/static/global/js/mapping-information.js`

### Test results
2418 passed, 15 skipped — 0 failures

