## Build pipeline — Lakeflow (managed_synced) silently skipped on cold start

### Context
`GlobalConfigService` keeps a 5-minute in-memory cache of the global config.
At cold start, if Lakebase was transiently unavailable, the cache was populated
with the empty template (`_empty()`). The Settings UI always uses `force=True`
(so it showed the correct persisted `managed_synced` value), but the build
pipeline did not — it received `{}` for `graph_engine_config`, saw no
`sync_mode`, and silently fell back to `app_managed`, skipping Lakeflow
entirely for up to 5 minutes after cold start.

### Changes
1. `src/back/core/triplestore/TripleStoreFactory.py` — added `force: bool = False`
   to `_read_global_config`, `_resolve_graph_engine`, and `_resolve_graph_engine_config`
2. `src/back/objects/digitaltwin/_build_pipeline.py` — `_resolve_lakebase_mode`
   now calls both resolver methods with `force=True`
3. `src/api/routers/internal/dtwin.py` — `start_triplestore_sync` step-list
   detection also uses `force=True` so task steps match what the pipeline executes

### Modified files
- `src/back/core/triplestore/TripleStoreFactory.py`
- `src/back/objects/digitaltwin/_build_pipeline.py`
- `src/api/routers/internal/dtwin.py`

### Test results
